text: Geraldine Feeney (born 9 September 1957) is a former Irish Fianna Fáil politician, who was a member of Seanad Éireann from 2002 to 2011. After standing unsuccessfully on the Cultural and Educational Panel in 1997, she was first elected by the Labour Panel in 2002 and was re-elected in 2007. She lost her seat at the 2011 Seanad election. ==References== Category:1957 births Category:Living people Category:Alumni of NUI Galway Category:Fianna Fáil senators Category:Members of the 22nd Seanad Category:Members of the 23rd Seanad Category:21st-century women members of Seanad Éireann Category:Politicians from County Offaly Category:Politicians from County Sligo
